signatures.description: The executable uses a known packer

T1045.long: Software packing is a method of compressing or encrypting an executable. Packing an executable changes the file signature in an attempt to avoid signature-based detection. Most decompression techniques decompress the executable code in memory.

strings: !This program cannot be run in DOS mode.
Write each FILE to standard output, with line numbers added.
With no FILE, or when FILE is -, read standard input.
-b, --body-numbering=STYLE      use STYLE for numbering body lines
-d, --section-delimiter=CC      use CC for separating logical pages
-f, --footer-numbering=STYLE    use STYLE for numbering footer lines
-h, --header-numbering=STYLE    use STYLE for numbering header lines
-i, --page-increment=NUMBER     line number increment at each line
-l, --join-blank-lines=NUMBER   group of NUMBER empty lines counted as one
-n, --number-format=FORMAT      insert line numbers according to FORMAT
-p, --no-renumber               do not reset line numbers at logical pages
-v, --first-page=NUMBER         first line number on each logical page
-w, --number-width=NUMBER       use NUMBER columns for line numbers
two delimiter characters for separating logical pages, a missing
second character implies :.  Type \\ for \.  STYLE is one of:
pREGEXP   number only lines that contain a match for REGEXP
ln   left justified, no leading zeros
rn   right justified, no leading zeros
